ON Wednesday, the 18th Instant, between Nine and Ten o'Clock in the Forenoon,
William Cavenagh ,
James McGennis , and
John Cross , in one Cart;
Mary Dymer ,
John Collison , and
George Aldridge , in another;
Bosavern Penlez ,
John Alford , and
James Arnold , in a Third;
Thomas Hazard , and
John Graham , in a Fourth;
David Boyd , and
Philip Lacy , in a Fifth;
Thomas Robinson , and
Thomas Mynott , in a Sixth, went to the Place of Execution. They came there about Eleven, with a very great Multitude of People; and having prayed some Time with them, and recommended their Souls to God, they were turned off from two Carts, calling on the Lord to have Mercy on them.
